there's no more horror in the hallways...

25:46.580 --> 25:49.504
You okay? What's wrong?

25:49.899 --> 25:51.688
Nothing.

26:01.256 --> 26:03.123
Five minutes.

26:03.223 --> 26:06.626
You guys couldn't act like a normal
goddamn family for five minutes.

26:06.726 --> 26:09.193
I think we're pretty normal
compared to those two.

26:09.293 --> 26:11.137
That creep deliberately baited Duncan.

26:11.495 --> 26:13.846
Sweetheart, it wasn't your fault.

26:13.946 --> 26:17.731
I don't know why your aunt got so mad
over some stupid piece of kitsch.

26:18.031 --> 26:21.332
She wasn't mad. She was scared.

26:21.432 --> 26:24.137
I can't believe you dragged us here
on Christmas Eve

26:24.237 --> 26:27.603
so that you could hustle your own aunt,
that is a new low, Taylor, even for you.

26:27.703 --> 26:28.787
It's not a hustle,

26:28.887 --> 26:32.954
the Bioplex is a means of integrating
technology into a sustainable future,

26:33.054 --> 26:37.410
where scientific innovation
is a shared experience.

26:37.510 --> 26:41.547
Fine, yeah, it's all good when it pays
for the house and the vacations

26:41.647 --> 26:46.739
and the school and the orthodontist,
but, otherwise, no, it's a big joke!

26:57.024 --> 26:58.846
Come on!

27:00.559 --> 27:03.116
Come on, come on.

27:06.297 --> 27:08.587
Damn, damn, damn!

27:10.667 --> 27:12.557
Seriously?

27:21.510 --> 27:25.047
I'm standing at the very spot
where Connor was found crucified

27:25.147 --> 27:28.682
exactly one year ago today
on Christmas Eve.

27:28.782 --> 27:32.653
Connor's neck was broken.
And over here...

27:33.453 --> 27:38.288
Jenna's mutilated body was found
hanging off some metal piping in the ceiling.

27:38.388 --> 27:40.822
Why would somebody go to so much effort?

27:40.922 --> 27:45.348
That is just one of the many unanswered
questions in this baffling case.

27:48.228 --> 27:49.662
How's it look?

27:49.762 --> 27:51.596
You guys...

27:51.696 --> 27:53.886
it's still here.

27:57.768 --> 28:00.570
Unto us a child is born.

28:00.670 --> 28:03.338
Unto us a son is given.

28:03.438 --> 28:05.238
That is fucking creepy.

28:05.338 --> 28:11.212
It's from Isaiah, Chapter 9,
Verse 6 about the birth of Jesus.

28:14.610 --> 28:17.278
Okay, this place is creeping me out.

28:17.378 --> 28:20.013
I think we've got everything
we need, let's go.

28:20.113 --> 28:22.586
Yeah, won't argue with you there.

28:40.031 --> 28:41.854
What the hell?

28:42.699 --> 28:44.133
What's wrong?

28:44.233 --> 28:46.736
What the fuck?
I could've sworn it was this one.

28:46.836 --> 28:49.291
Molly, come on, hurry up.

28:50.470 --> 28:52.260
Move.

28:53.039 --> 28:56.373
I tried them all three times,
none of them fit.

28:56.473 --> 28:58.163
Crap.

29:01.778 --> 29:03.512
Okay.

29:04.512 --> 29:06.336
Hello?

29:06.681 --> 29:08.771
Principal Harod!

29:10.284 --> 29:13.042
Principal Harod? Hello?

29:14.054 --> 29:16.088
Principal Harod!

29:16.188 --> 29:18.024
Fuck!

29:18.124 --> 29:20.813
Of course now, he isn't around.

29:24.427 --> 29:25.662
Can't see anything.

29:25.762 --> 29:28.625
I've got full bars and some service,
it should be ringing.

29:29.344 --> 29:30.735
Really?

29:31.331 --> 29:34.622
Guys, what if Principal Harod
locked us in?

29:35.034 --> 29:36.802
Why would he do that?

29:36.902 --> 29:39.742
For all we know,
he could be down here with us.

29:41.072 --> 29:43.362
I got nothing, too.

29:53.616 --> 29:55.417
Come on, baby.

29:55.517 --> 29:57.406
Smile.

29:59.019 --> 30:01.997
Will... you okay?

30:03.189 --> 30:06.658
Sport, don't just sit there. Look like
you've never seen a Christmas tree before.

30:06.758 --> 30:09.148
Why don't you help
your old man, all right?

30:20.303 --> 30:23.477
I like that one. Okay, I'll do it.

30:27.108 --> 30:29.398
Right there.

30:38.451 --> 30:41.575
I wasn't around much
last Christmas, I know.

30:42.988 --> 30:45.445
This year we're having fun, right?

31:00.170 --> 31:02.227
Slow down, Will.

31:25.161 --> 31:27.879
Looks like someone's
worked up an appetite.

31:28.746 --> 31:31.231
That's his second serving.

31:31.331 --> 31:35.289
It must be good.
It's making me hungry, let's eat.

31:38.503 --> 31:41.627
You're eating too fast,
you're gonna get a tummy ache.

31:44.807 --> 31:46.508
Hey.

31:46.708 --> 31:49.232
Will, you hear your mother
talking to you?

31:52.279 --> 31:54.370
All right, I think that's enough.

31:54.682 --> 31:57.040
- Damn it! What the fuck?
- Scott, no!

32:04.757 --> 32:06.625
I'll handle it.

32:06.725 --> 32:10.005
Yeah, you handle it.
What's wrong with that kid?

32:14.698 --> 32:16.754
Why'd you do that?

32:18.400 --> 32:19.627
Answer me!

32:23.937 --> 32:26.294
Go to your room right now!

32:41.020 --> 32:44.524
Christmas, the most
magical time of year,

32:44.624 --> 32:48.122
but in Bailey Downs this Christmas...

32:48.222 --> 32:50.310
it's different.

32:50.927 --> 32:54.629
It's gotta be. It's true,
my friends, and you know it is.

32:54.729 --> 32:57.699
So before I put another jingle
in your stocking,

32:57.799 --> 33:01.604
I want you to think about
the little ones in your life

33:01.704 --> 33:05.859
and give a thought to the little ones
who aren't with us anymore.

33:07.705 --> 33:11.641
Yeah, this next one's for them.
For Jenna.

33:12.841 --> 33:14.698
And Connor.

33:14.876 --> 33:20.436
From Saint Joseph's Academy
taken from us last year cruelly.

33:21.631 --> 33:24.049
I know they're listening.

33:24.149 --> 33:26.645
Somewhere out there.

33:56.540 --> 33:58.897
Martha, thank God!

34:00.109 --> 34:01.710
What's going on?

34:01.810 --> 34:05.835
It's the elves, I fear
they may all become infected.

34:06.547 --> 34:09.902
Infected? What do you mean?

34:10.648 --> 34:14.071
- Others are sick?
- It's worse than that.

34:15.751 --> 34:18.853
- What happened?
- Shiny's body is gone.

34:19.152 --> 34:24.007
He was laid to rest, but now...
it may already be too late.

34:24.107 --> 34:26.190
But this doesn't make any sense.

34:26.291 --> 34:31.617
Elves becoming the walking dead?
No, it does not make any sense.

34:31.717 --> 34:34.920
Unless he is behind it.

34:36.396 --> 34:38.356
Stand back, Martha!

34:44.472 --> 34:46.262
You need to hide!

34:46.674 --> 34:50.598
Open up, you fat fucking piece of shit!

34:51.275 --> 34:53.277
Here's Shiny!

34:53.377 --> 34:55.504
- Shiny risen from the dead!
- What?

34:55.603 --> 35:00.103
- Quick, go, hide!
- Where's my fucking cookie?

35:04.636 --> 35:06.825
Stay back, Jingles!

35:10.323 --> 35:13.914
Yeah. Yeah, I got you, you cocksucker!

35:14.025 --> 35:16.615
Motherfucker, oh, shit!

35:34.375 --> 35:38.143
- I didn't find any windows without bars.
- Same here.

35:38.243 --> 35:39.418
Guys, I can't be here,

35:39.518 --> 35:42.514
I'm supposed to be at the mall helping
with the food drive or mom's gonna kill me.

35:42.614 --> 35:45.216
We've all got places to be,
it's Christmas Eve, bro.

35:45.316 --> 35:47.839
There's gotta be
another way out of here.

35:58.661 --> 36:00.617
Oh, God.

36:17.244 --> 36:19.467
A little jumpy, Dylan?

36:23.460 --> 36:27.452
This is a nativity scene.
The school didn't put it up this year.

36:27.552 --> 36:30.353
You can't openly display
a nativity scene anymore.

36:30.453 --> 36:32.859
It's the war on Christmas.

36:34.621 --> 36:37.347
Damn it, more bars.

36:39.191 --> 36:41.247
Fuck, it's freezing down here.

36:42.693 --> 36:44.216
I can hear it.

36:47.396 --> 36:49.119
Damn thing is on.

36:58.405 --> 37:00.239
It won't...

37:00.839 --> 37:01.906
heat up.

37:02.006 --> 37:06.539
Look, if we just sit around and wait it out,
I'm sure that somebody is gonna notice.

37:06.639 --> 37:09.310
Only Caprice knows we're down here
and she's out of town.

37:09.410 --> 37:11.712
The school's not gonna reopen
for another week and a half.

37:11.812 --> 37:16.382
Look... if there was ever a time
to notice three missing kids,

37:16.482 --> 37:19.172
tonight would be it, right?

37:19.650 --> 37:21.907
We always open one gift.

37:26.188 --> 37:28.511
Every Christmas Eve.

37:29.457 --> 37:31.747
We eat pizza with champagne.

37:33.793 --> 37:35.823
Watch The Sound of Music.

37:36.194 --> 37:38.484
Before we go to bed...

37:40.730 --> 37:43.254
we each open one gift.

37:44.600 --> 37:46.622
Not this year.

37:48.970 --> 37:51.394
Hell of a Christmas?

37:56.476 --> 37:58.310
Hey.

37:58.410 --> 38:01.066
It's not pizza and champagne, but...

38:03.012 --> 38:05.779
- Merry Christmas.
- Thanks, Dylan.

38:05.879 --> 38:08.703
I didn't realize how starving I am.

38:09.114 --> 38:10.604
Yeah.

38:11.783 --> 38:13.473
What if he comes back?

38:14.418 --> 38:16.019
Who?

38:16.319 --> 38:19.355
The guy who killed Jenna and Connor,
what if he comes back tonight?

38:19.455 --> 38:21.723
I mean, we're trapped down here.

38:21.823 --> 38:25.884
- And there's a psychopath on the loose.
- Psycho's already here.

38:25.984 --> 38:29.463
Principal Harod. I'm sure he locked
the door on us, who else could it be?

38:29.563 --> 38:33.962
I get that he's creepy, okay?
But that doesn't mean he's a killer.

38:34.062 --> 38:37.154
Then what's he doing here?
On Christmas Eve?

38:39.434 --> 38:42.505
What makes matters worse, I gotta piss.

38:53.313 --> 38:56.170
I'm sure Joe won't mind...

38:56.582 --> 38:58.572
if I borrow this.

39:12.563 --> 39:14.892
What is this place?

39:40.055 --> 39:43.713
Caprice will know something's up
when Dylan doesn't call her tonight.

39:48.946 --> 39:51.453
What is that fucking smell?

40:06.444 --> 40:08.701
Do you hear that?

40:36.570 --> 40:38.427
What is it?

40:48.446 --> 40:50.235
What is it?

40:51.964 --> 40:53.621
I don't know.

41:16.936 --> 41:18.959
It stopped.

41:26.777 --> 41:29.246
Molly, Molly, come on!

41:29.346 --> 41:30.518
What's going on?

41:30.618 --> 41:33.149
I don't know. I don't know.
She started freaking and twitching!

41:33.249 --> 41:35.789
Molly!

42:19.457 --> 42:21.714
Will! Get out!

42:33.035 --> 42:34.725
Hey.

42:35.637 --> 42:37.360
Hey.

42:37.938 --> 42:41.456
- How's your hand?
- I'll live.

42:41.556 --> 42:44.342
Have you noticed Will
hasn't had to use his inhaler?

42:44.442 --> 42:46.765
Really? That's a good thing, right?

42:48.210 --> 42:49.889
Yeah.

42:50.245 --> 42:53.202
Something seems wrong.

42:53.547 --> 42:58.217
- Maybe we should take him to the doctor?
- The doctor? On Christmas Eve?

42:58.317 --> 43:00.306
Maybe we should just keep an eye on him.

43:00.886 --> 43:02.675
Come here.

43:05.656 --> 43:07.702
You know...

43:07.802 --> 43:10.462
they say you're allowed to open
one gift before Christmas.

43:16.832 --> 43:18.722
Scott...

43:22.570 --> 43:24.504
Not right now.

43:24.604 --> 43:27.461
All right, I just figured,
you know, it's...

43:27.572 --> 43:30.140
- it's been awhile.
- What's going on?

43:30.240 --> 43:32.309
What's going on with me?
What are you saying?

43:32.409 --> 43:34.844
I mean with Will.
The way he's been acting.

43:34.944 --> 43:37.878
Yeah, sure, whatever.
You know what, forget it.

43:37.978 --> 43:39.901
No, wait.

43:56.594 --> 43:57.998
<i>Yes!</i>

43:58.098 --> 44:00.330
<i>"Dangerous" Dan!</i>

44:00.430 --> 44:04.355
<i>Let's listen to this Christmas classic.</i>

46:11.314 --> 46:13.215
We should have stayed on the road.

46:13.315 --> 46:16.685
Didn't exactly wear my "trudging
through the woods" boots.

46:16.785 --> 46:19.587
Look, this will help us shave
a half hour off our walk back to Etta's,

46:19.687 --> 46:22.289
plus I gave you all the option
of staying in the car.

46:22.389 --> 46:26.324
Yeah, where mom and I would be easy prey
for drunk hillbilly rapists, no thanks, Dad.

46:26.424 --> 46:28.927
- We should make weapons.
- What?

46:29.027 --> 46:32.594
In case whatever dad nearly hit
comes and hunts us. The sun has set,

46:32.694 --> 46:36.431
it is officially Krampusnacht,
the night of Krampus.

46:36.531 --> 46:39.389
Son, that Krampus
is a load of old German bull...

46:41.392 --> 46:42.875
Dad!

46:43.171 --> 46:45.710
Oh, my God, what happened?

46:46.206 --> 46:48.096
Oh, my God, you're bleeding!

46:50.225 --> 46:52.832
- Am I shot?
- I don't know!

46:54.978 --> 46:58.669
Oh, my God. Duncan, get back here!

47:05.386 --> 47:07.142
Duncan!

47:15.193 --> 47:16.583
I got it!

47:20.797 --> 47:22.793
- Oh, my God! Duncan!
- Oh, my God, Duncan!

47:22.893 --> 47:24.940
Duncan!

47:25.662 --> 47:28.809
- Duncan!
- Duncan!

47:31.071 --> 47:33.506
Duncan, where are you?

47:33.606 --> 47:36.023
- Duncan!
- Answer me!

47:37.074 --> 47:38.864
Duncan?

47:42.845 --> 47:44.268
Duncan?

47:51.585 --> 47:53.108
Duncan?

48:06.163 --> 48:07.876
- Oh, my God!
- Where is he?

48:07.976 --> 48:10.267
I don't know. I don't know.

48:10.367 --> 48:13.491
- We need the police.
- Mom, there's no service out here.

48:15.803 --> 48:18.304
- What is that?
- Come on.

48:19.686 --> 48:21.175
Run!

48:22.073 --> 48:24.129
We have to run.

48:25.342 --> 48:27.032
Duncan?

48:53.600 --> 48:55.290
Sparkles!

48:55.802 --> 48:57.058
Sparkles!

49:31.300 --> 49:35.304
I'm gonna eat your fucking brains out,
you Christmas cunt.

49:35.404 --> 49:37.660
Fuck you!

49:38.205 --> 49:42.763
I'll break that fucking staff
in your rosy-cheeked ass, you fucker!

49:44.975 --> 49:47.465
I'm sorry, Shiny.

49:48.077 --> 49:50.346
I know it isn't your fault.

49:50.446 --> 49:53.370
You don't have
the Christmas balls, you...

49:58.819 --> 50:02.689
Bailey Downs, it's getting close there
and we're counting down to Christmas

50:02.789 --> 50:06.550
and "Dangerous" Dan
is pulling his annual double shift

50:06.650 --> 50:09.126
to stay with you until the end.

50:09.226 --> 50:10.949
What?

50:11.661 --> 50:14.863
What, we're... Okay,
well we're gonna check in

50:14.963 --> 50:18.531
with good ol' Stormin' Norman
down at the charity food drive.

50:18.631 --> 50:22.756
Hey, Norman! Normey, you're a little...

50:22.856 --> 50:24.417
little scratchy there, buddy.

50:24.517 --> 50:29.026
What, I did press the button, Susan.
Why don't you press your own button?

50:33.473 --> 50:37.177
Sorry, folks, looks like we got some of
those winter weather technical difficulties,

50:37.277 --> 50:40.316
too many reindeer in the atmosphere.

50:41.411 --> 50:46.737
That's my bet, so let's...
throw another eggnog on the fire.

50:47.115 --> 50:51.995
No, wait a minute, let's...
let's throw another log on the fire

50:52.095 --> 50:53.922
and pour yourself another eggnog.

50:54.322 --> 50:57.691
You know, get some good Christmas vibes.

50:57.791 --> 51:02.395
Out to Susan who is seriously
harshing my buzz right now.

51:02.495 --> 51:08.288
<i>And listen to this holly jolly classic.</i>

51:25.082 --> 51:26.904
Little shit.

51:27.249 --> 51:28.950
Will.

51:29.150 --> 51:30.873
Will!

51:31.251 --> 51:33.252
Will, where are you?

51:33.734 --> 51:36.176
- What is it?
- Where is he?

51:37.320 --> 51:39.254
Where is he? Will?

51:39.354 --> 51:42.377
- There you are.
- Baby, don't... don't!

51:42.555 --> 51:46.124
Did you open those presents? Did you?

51:46.324 --> 51:48.447
- Say something!
- Scott!

51:49.993 --> 51:53.094
- You think this is a game?
- What are you doing?

51:53.194 --> 51:56.651
Say something. Look at him,
think it's all one big fucking joke!

51:56.751 --> 51:58.225
- Scott!
- You think this is funny?

51:58.325 --> 51:59.333
- No!
- Move!

51:59.433 --> 52:03.573
No! No! No! Don't! Stop!

52:03.673 --> 52:05.170
I knew this would happen!

52:05.270 --> 52:07.772
You refused to see a doctor,
you said you could handle it!

52:07.872 --> 52:10.190
I... did you not see what he did?

52:10.290 --> 52:11.945
Get out!

52:36.595 --> 52:38.818
Will, you all right?

52:49.305 --> 52:53.341
- Hello?
- <i>Is this the Peters household?</i>

52:53.441 --> 52:55.109
Yes.

52:55.209 --> 52:58.578
<i>Got yourself a nice
Christmas tree, did you?</i>

52:58.678 --> 52:59.747
Who is this?

52:59.947 --> 53:03.082
You don't know me, just consider me
a concerned neighbor.

53:03.382 --> 53:06.418
<i>You were on my land,
took one of my trees,</i>

53:06.518 --> 53:09.041
<i>and I saw your license plate.</i>

53:10.354 --> 53:11.621
What do you want?

53:11.721 --> 53:15.446
Your boy, how is he? Did something
happen to him in the grove?

53:19.260 --> 53:21.636
- Look, I don't know...
- <i>I said...</i>

53:21.736 --> 53:25.052
<i>did something happen to your boy.</i>

53:25.530 --> 53:28.354
He got lost, but we found him later.

53:29.366 --> 53:32.533
No, you didn't. He's still lost.

53:32.833 --> 53:36.085
<i>Now we haven't got much time,
so you're gonna have to do as I say.</i>

53:36.385 --> 53:40.326
Bring the changeling back to the forest
where you lost your son.

53:41.838 --> 53:44.677
Changeling? What the hell is that?

53:45.007 --> 53:48.508
Ma'am... that ain't your son.

53:54.980 --> 53:57.871
- Don't call again.
- <i>Wait, wait!</i>

54:40.154 --> 54:41.977
Molly?

54:45.057 --> 54:48.326
We... were worried about you.

54:48.426 --> 54:52.095
- What is it? You okay?
- Just come.

54:52.195 --> 54:54.551
I have to show you something.

54:59.234 --> 55:01.357
Should I wake Ben?

55:05.472 --> 55:07.662
Where are you going?

55:09.959 --> 55:11.649
Molly?

55:12.411 --> 55:14.167
Okay.

55:35.467 --> 55:37.779
You kidding me?

55:43.406 --> 55:45.096
Molly.

55:50.245 --> 55:51.535
Wait.

55:53.047 --> 55:55.137
You're serious?

55:58.645 --> 56:00.475
Okay.

56:01.521 --> 56:04.378
Molly. Molly, Molly, Molly.

56:05.490 --> 56:09.381
Hey, this isn't gonna happen, Molly,
I have a girlfriend.

56:11.778 --> 56:14.509
I think you're in shock or something.

57:21.426 --> 57:23.082
Will?

57:28.432 --> 57:30.122
Will?

57:34.370 --> 57:36.427
Will, is that you?

57:58.326 --> 58:00.550
I shouldn't have lost my head
like that, I'm sorry.

58:06.433 --> 58:08.394
Dad's just...

58:08.494 --> 58:10.998
been a little stressed lately.

58:13.772 --> 58:17.562
But I'm trying. I'm trying to be better.

59:00.813 --> 59:02.236
Scott?

59:49.254 --> 59:51.043
Hurry!

59:59.260 --> 01:00:00.270
Hurry!

01:00:02.996 --> 01:00:05.303
Get in. In, in.

01:00:15.373 --> 01:00:18.890
Pull him here, get him here. Okay.

01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:20.659
Okay.

01:00:28.584 --> 01:00:30.652
Do you think that you could walk?

01:00:30.752 --> 01:00:32.754
We have to find Duncan.

01:00:32.854 --> 01:00:35.489
- Yeah, I can go, I can go.
- Dad, no, you can't.

01:00:35.889 --> 01:00:38.258
Mom, we have to stay here,
something's still out there.

01:00:38.358 --> 01:00:40.914
He is out there by himself.

01:00:41.759 --> 01:00:44.316
Mom, what if it really is Krampus?

01:00:44.928 --> 01:00:46.863
We have to stay in this church
until sunrise.

01:00:46.963 --> 01:00:49.266
- That is insane, let's go.
- Yeah, it is.

01:00:49.366 --> 01:00:53.389
Church, church,
we have to confess our sins.

01:00:54.068 --> 01:00:57.853
I'm not gonna make it to sunrise,
